op1: I seek out monogamous people who want to get to know each other a little bit before we’d decide to hook up. Almost every time, we get along really well and decide to be friends instead.
op2: I’d attribute my success to the girl I matched with being a friend of a friend, so we already kind of knew each other and the app was like the bridge finally bringing us together. I think the failures are because apps are so easy to just open and close, and not respond to, especially as a college student. I have a demanding major and am a student athlete, and that is usually the same demographic of my matches, so we’re always super busy and it’s hard to get things started.
op3: I’m strictly monogamous and a survivor of SA, so I’m very careful about who I hookup with. I prefer short term over one night stand, so I can make sure I like the person, and so it can come to more of a natural close rather than “okay I had a fun night” and then I’d see them still and only be able to think of that one night. Using a dating app was so important for my first WLW experience. I couldn’t out myself to all my friends yet or find anyone in my close community, so meeting someone on an app gave me freedom and choice.
op4: I’ve always been more chill with WLW situationships than het ones (I’m F/NB and Bi), and it’s nice that on apps, it’s easy to find people who are also a little nervous like I am, but want to get together and try it.
